<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-01-0413 </DOCNO><TEXT>The dynamical breakdown of chiral symmetry in a finite Abelian gauge theoryusing a variational approach for the effective potential for compositeoperators is discussed. It is shown that, at least in a variational approach,the fermion either remains massless or gets a dynamical mass for everynon-zero coupling constant.</TEXT></DOC>